"{\"uid\": \"newsday.co.tt-2024-08-04-american-noah-lyles-wins-mens-olympic-100m-title-in-photo-finish\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The \\\"fastest man in the world\\\" debate has been raging for weeks, long before the track and field segment of the 2024 Paris Olympic Games got started this week.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a dramatic men's 100-metre final at the Stade de France on August 4, USA's Noah Lyles, the reigning 100m and 200m world champion, had an emphatic say in the argument when he edged Jamaica's Kishane Thompson by 0.005 seconds to take the Olympic title.\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9983687373543424, \"rank\": 0.001023456407377692, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999998956355, \"rank\": 1.0221811701312034e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9993505772205638, \"rank\": 0.0006498448028235754, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a tense final which saw all eight athletes dipping under the ten-second barrier, Lyles clocked a time of 9.784 seconds, with Thompson clocking 9.789.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999999767810552, \"rank\": 2.3215431861099532e-08, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9993505772205638, \"rank\": 0.0006498448028235754, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both athletes were officially given a time of 9.79, with Lyles' late surge and critical dip at the line proving to be the difference between the two sprinters in a tense photo-finish.\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999999767810552, \"rank\": 2.3215431861099532e-08, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Running out of lane seven, Lyles, who was beaten earlier in the day in the first semifinal by Jamaica's Oblique Seville, looked to be out of contention midway through the final as both Thompson and USA's Fred Kerley led the pack.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999999767810552, \"rank\": 2.3215431861099532e-08, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": 